ANALYSIS
========

PROGRESS vs M9.R.28:
- M9.R.28's smoke never reached a logged-in shell; the malformed
  shadow hash + tty1-only autologin meant `localhost login:` prompted
  forever on serial console. M9.R.28 marked Gap 8 CLOSED prematurely.
- M9.R.29 captures the FIRST verified live-ISO DE smoke transcript.
  All four DE binaries land at /usr/bin/{sway,kwin_wayland,mutter,
  plasmashell} as symlinks to the from-source install-mirrors.

PROGRESS vs the prior M9.R.29 attempt (5/6, no symlink walker):
- plasmashell: WAS libgcc_s.so.1 not found
              IS  libmount.so.1 not found
  M9.R.29.19's symlink walker correctly pulled gcc-14.3.0-libgcc into
  the closure so libgcc_s.so.1 resolves; the new failure exposes the
  next missing prefix.

REMAINING M9.R.29 HONEST GAP (smaller than M9.R.28):
- The DE binaries' baked RPATH lists from-source install dirs but
  doesn't always include the transitive runtime libs (util-linux's
  libmount, zlib's libz, libdrm, libglvnd's libGLESv2). These come
  from M9.R.14f's LD_LIBRARY_PATH-reflected RPATH mechanism, but at
  the bottom of the chain some pkg-config deps (e.g. plasma-workspace
  doesn't pull in util-linux's libmount) silently leave their .so
  off the RPATH chain.
- Build-host `ldd` for each DE binary reports the same set of unmet
  deps — this is a PRE-EXISTING recipe-architecture gap that lands
  unchanged on the ISO; it's NOT caused by stage-de-rootfs.
- The M9.R.29 closure walker fix correctly stages every nix-store
  prefix the on-disk RPATHs reference. What's missing is the
  recipe-side RPATH entries pointing at util-linux/zlib/libdrm/libglvnd.
  A follow-up needs to either patchelf-extend the binaries with the
  transitive paths OR enforce buildDep transitivity at link time.

SUCCESSES CAPTURED
==================
- M9.R.29.16 (shadow hash): root login works at multi-user.
- M9.R.29.17 (serial-getty autologin): tty1 + ttyS0 both autologin.
- M9.R.29.19 (symlink closure walker): gcc-libgcc + companion
  multi-output -lib/-libgcc nix paths land on the ISO; plasmashell
  no longer crashes at libgcc_s.so.1.
